				<td colspan="2"><span>Raffeling wrote:
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Sony won't even tell what the bugs are.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
From what I can tell, Sony has a policy of not admitting bugs until they are fixed on Test.  I guess part of of the motivation for that is reduce the amount of exploitation, and to reduce the pressure on them to fix it.
<br />

<br />
For example, how long has the bard bug been in where you re-sing a song and just as it activates it drops?  Since day one as far as I can tell.  This bug can't be exploited, but since they've never admitted this problem, they feel little motivation to fix it.  (or perhaps they do, but have not found a good solution for it yet, who knows...)
<br />

<br />
Also, if there were a list of bugs somewhere, a competitor could link to their list, saying &quot;look how many bugs are in Everquest!&quot;
<br />
</span></td>
